            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I've been paying this game since i was 13 and i came at a time when the bot crisis started arising, even then i had a lot of fun and to this day still keep coming back. The amount of unique people I've met and the evolution of the game growing more and more and then coming together when there's a major problem was kinda amazing. I both hate and love this game with my very soul."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "227294467",
            "steam_id": "76561198416826599",
            "playtime_minutes": 9532,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Valve for the love of all that is Holy, Please Remove Auto-Balance from the game\nIt has never helped a server come back from player loss\nIt also really likes changing my team to a team that will lose in 2 seconds and cost me the game\nIt is a system that was Obsolete in 2008 when the game came out\nand its just an annoying Relic now"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "227215575",
            "steam_id": "76561198070226860",
            "playtime_minutes": 116176,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "This game is very fun and most of the community is pretty good, but the new player experience is absolutely atrocious. Do not start playing this game without either a friend to walk you through things or a new player guide to help you both with the settings and with the general gameplay. The \"tutorial\" is a joke, the matchmaking is a joke, and the official \"competitive\" is a joke. I would personally recommend playing on a community server instead of a casual server. There are many to chose from and there are no wrong answers as long as you are having fun, but I personally prefer Uncletopia since those servers are often very populated. Again though, there are no wrong answers for what server to play on as long as you are having fun."
        },
